entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i would love to hear about one of your trips

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i worked on cruise ships as a musical entertainer and traveled to alaska the aleutian islands korea japan and the caribbean islands

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: awesome what is one of your most memorable experiences

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: being in galena alaska and being on a small airplane and traveling in a snow storm and surviving

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: wow how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: like i was on the edge of death and life but i lived

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what did you study at school

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the arts and business

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you decide to do that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not know i was attracted to the arts at a young age and business went along with it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: sometimes when i am feeling tense i turn on the fish tank screensaver hey i know it is not hawaii but it is the best i have got what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i listen to music and i sit with my girlfriend and she calms me down when i am stressed out

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: aw how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i could work on that i am not very good at that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: last night with my girlfriend she was asking my advice on something and as i was speaking to her she felt my tone of voice was too loud i was not angry but i was irritated that i was being told to quiet down when i did not really wanna help i just wanted to relax

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sucks

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i agree

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: sometimes when things do not go my way i get depressed or upset and i wish i could calm down and just realize that i should count my blessings and look at the bright side of everything no matter how bad things get always look at the bright side that is my goal

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how hard is that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is been very difficult but i am working on it and it seems to be getting a little easier

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is so good to hear tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well when i was taking care of my mother and she was dying of copd and then it turned into lung cancer i chose not to tell her that her condition had worsened so she would not be fearful and i had to sit knowing that her symptoms were getting worse but i could not tell her the truth and i let her think that everything was okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: wow that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my mother being sick and dependent on oxygen for three years and me seeing her health decline that is what plagues me the most in my dreams and in my thoughts if i could erase that if that never happened i would feel better

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh i do not know i try to be grateful i am alive and try to focus on my own objectives and not dwell on the negative things of my memory

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my girlfriend she is a very good positive positive influence she wants me to be a better person

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: she since i met her she is been trying to make me not be angry to make me not feel negative and to be a nurturing positive zen like man so what she is asking for is something that is gonna make me improve therefore i must capitulate

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is very easy i sleep well sometimes i wake up when i have nightmares about my mother or something but i go back to sleep

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: that is unknown i do not know it just happens

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have been feeling good eh the my reality is i have been hit with a lot of financial problems but i am handling handling them well actually

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have been looking at it as my girlfriend has told me that i need to do this so therefore it is on the forefront of my mind right now

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: today when i woke up and it was a sunny beautiful day and i had a lot of goals to achieve and i am achieving each one one by one it gives me a sense of accomplishment and happiness

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great tell me how you spend your ideal weekend

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my ideal weekend would be playing music with my girlfriend as that is something we enjoy to do healthy going out to a nice dinner of healthy food and maybe exercising and feeling good with my body and mind and spirit

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about something you did recently that you really enjoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well everything i do i enjoy it is hard to to pick out one exact event that i really enjoyed i do not know how to put one above the other

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: when things do not go my way and finances xxx come down and i do not get jobs that i go for that i am qualified for but i feel i am not getting my fair chance at opportunity it is very frustrating

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: it can be tough to find a good job these days what is something you feel guilty about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not really feel guilty about things sometimes maybe if i am angry and i should not be i feel guilty about that i do not ever wanna be short with my girlfriend ever she would not does not deserve somebody using vulgar language or shouting or something so i do not wanna be that way around her so therefore that i am guilty

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you most proud of in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my achievements of my abilities through my music and my other abilities that i have and of my hard work has paid off and i am very proud of those

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay i think i have asked everything i need to thanks for sharing your thoughts with me

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: okay thank you
